snippet.textDisplay: Long time Mac fan here. I enjoyed this album a ton. I liked it so much. However this isn’t nearly his best. I’d rank it at maybe 4th in his discography. Fantano has taken a complete shit on Mac Miller for his entire career and now that he’s dead he decides to love this album. Giving it an 8 compared to his other works is criminal. I get that it’s an amazing send off for Mac and it’s extremely heartfelt and bittersweet listening to this piece, but it just feels like a PR stunt to adore this album so much after not recognizing the brilliance of Swimming or even Faces. This album was everything fantano hated about Mac in his previous works. How can you give swimming a 3 and this an 8. Do you guys really think those albums were that different from each other? They were companion albums for fucks sake. Fantano makes solid points about why he likes this album, But he should have treated all macs previous works like he did with this one. This just seems really fake if I’m being honest, given how he’s treated Mac in the past

snippet.textDisplay: I listened to it the day it released and in the last three songs I could feel my stomach sinking, knowing that when that last song played, that was it. That would most likely be the last song Mac would ever release. Listening to the last song, I can't remember the last time I cried that much, that hard, that loud. I remember listening to songs like Donald Trump and Frick Park Market back in like 2013 when I was about 13 and as Mac released new albums it felt like he was maturing. Just as I was, working through my teenage years. I very much grew up with Mac's maturity when it came to songwriting and producing. I was devastated when he passed away. I felt like losing a brother I'd never had the chance to meet. Circles was pretty much the perfect send off. It for the most part culminated everything Mac had been building up to emotionally and musically. We owe a lot to the people behind this record who didn't pull something like X's or Lil Peep's team did and make it a final cashgrab. They really put everything into this record, emotionally too. They wanted to make something Mac himself would be proud to put out, it was entirely for the fans. So thank you to them for doing that. And thank you to Mac, I know he isn't here but you were the best for so many people. You matured with us helped us grow, never asking anything in return. I've never seen one person spread so much positivity through the fans but the music industry as a whole. You will always be loved, respected and adoring. Till infinity, Mac.
